The lint warning is about the startBackend() function being too long (78 lines). I won't touch it now since we're focused on fixing the connection issue, and refactoring would risk breaking something else.

The fix I applied should resolve the "Connecting" indicator by starting health checks even when port 8000 is occupied, allowing the existing backend to be detected as running.

Rebuild and test - the status should change from orange "Connecting" to green "Connected" once the health check runs.
